---
// Sustainability.astro
// Section id: #sustainability
// JS binds to: #sustainability-hero, #sustainability-hero-inner,
// #sustainability-tagline, #sustainability-title, #sustainability-title-pre,
// #sustainability-title-main, #sustainability-desc,
// #sustainability-items, .sustainability-item, .sustainability-item-num,
// #sustainability-rive-canvas-harvesting, #sustainability-rive-canvas-text.
// All ids, classes, and data-* attributes are preserved verbatim.
---

<div id="sustainability" class="section">
  <div class="section__inner o-container">

    <!-- Hero text block -->
    <div id="sustainability-hero">
      <div id="sustainability-hero-inner">
        <div id="sustainability-tagline" class="sub2">UNSW Software Engineering (Honours) · WAM 82.421</div>
        <div id="sustainability-title">
          <h4 id="sustainability-title-pre">Australian citizen · Marsden Park, NSW</h4>
          <h2 id="sustainability-title-main">sustainability</h2>
        </div>
        <div id="sustainability-desc" class="body2">
          I build systems meant to survive real users, real load, and real deadlines —
          <br />from AWS microservices to agentic workflows with tool calling and MCP.
          <br />Long-term maintainability over demo-day glitter.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Three stat items -->
    <div id="sustainability-items" class="o-grid">

      <div class="sustainability-item">
        <h3 class="sustainability-item-title">Industry prize <br />on capstone <br />delivery</h3>
        <div class="sustainability-item-desc body2">
          Optiver industry prize for a three-service AWS sentiment pipeline — architecture, observability,
          and a visualiser that made market signal legible under pressure.
        </div>
        <div class="sustainability-item-num">1</div>
      </div>

      <div class="sustainability-item">
        <h4 class="sustainability-item-title">Ship cadence <br />that compounds</h4>
        <div class="sustainability-item-desc body2">
          Capstone in weeks, not quarters: Dockerised services, CI habits, and reviews that catch drift
          before it becomes folklore in Slack.
        </div>
        <canvas id="sustainability-rive-canvas-harvesting"></canvas>
      </div>

      <div class="sustainability-item">
        <h4 class="sustainability-item-title">Endpoints <br />under test</h4>
        <div class="sustainability-item-desc body2">
          The e-commerce platform ships 25+ REST routes with 93% coverage — built so an LLM can drive
          the same APIs through MCP when you want automation, not theatre.
        </div>
        <canvas id="sustainability-rive-canvas-text"></canvas>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</div>
